"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Dez 19, 2025</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104her1665702682608.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/her1665702682608.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/her1665702682608.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"her1665702682608\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Security Drivers and the Security Driver API\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"her1665702682608__security_drivers_and_the_security_driver_api_125867\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"her1665702682608__p_d40244e1_d40245e1_d40246e1\">Uniface provides security drivers of two types:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"her1665702682608__li_d20120e1_d20121e1_d20122e1\">Client/Server security driver—encode and decode connect messages and message header data that are exchanged between the Uniface client and Uniface Router.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"her1665702682608__li_d20123e1_d20124e1_d20125e1\">Email security drivers for SMTP and POP3 authentication—negotiate authentication via a SASL (Simple Authentication and Security Layer) mechanism.\n </li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"her1665702682608__p_d40247e1_d40248e1_d40249e1\">These security drivers are implementations of the Uniface Security Driver API, which you can use to create your own security driver. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"aqt1665702677943.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/aqt1665702677943.html\" title=\"Uniface provides an API for creating custom client/server and SMTP and POP security drivers. The API include files for the C compiler and libraries are provided in the Uniface/3gl directory.\">APIs: Security Driver</a>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"her1665702682608__p_d40250e1_d40251e1_d40252e1\">To help you use the API, the C source files for the\n         security drivers are available as a sample on <a class=\"xref\" href=\"https://community.rocketsoftware.com/uniface-samples-111\" rel=\"external noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Rocket Community</a>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"her1665702682608__p_d40256e1_d40257e1_d40258e1\">The compiled libraries for the drivers provided by Uniface are located in the <span class=\"ph filepath\">/common/bin</span> (Windows) or <span class=\"ph filepath\">/common/lib</span> (Unix) directory of your Uniface installation.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"her1665702682608__p_d40259e1_d40260e1_d40261e1\">To make a security driver available to your application, you must specify the library and entry point in the [USER_3GL] section of the assignment file. For example:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">[USER_3GL]\n; C/S security driver:C:/Program Files (x86)/Uniface10/bin/zsecdrv(usecappl)\n; OAuth 2.0 security drivers for email:C:/Program Files (x86)/Uniface10/bin//uauthxoauth2(UAuthXOAUTH2POP, UAuthXOAUTH2SMTP)</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div></div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/aqt1665702677943.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>APIs: Security Driver</a><p>Uniface provides an API for creating custom client/server and SMTP and POP security drivers. The API include files for the C compiler and libraries are provided in the Uniface/3gl directory.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/mce1665702677060.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>SMTP and POP3 Email</a><p>Uniface provides support for sending and receiving email using the SMTP and POP protocols over TCP/IP or TLS.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/cru1665702678159.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Security Context</a><p>A security context is the complete security environment required for a secure connection to a mail server. It consists of one or more security drivers that are responsible for connection and authentication to the email server.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528178\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528178\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Security Drivers and the Security Driver API Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Dez 19, 2025 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Security Drivers and the Security Driver API Uniface provides security drivers of two types: Client/Server security driver—encode and decode connect messages and message header data that are exchanged between the Uniface client and Uniface Router. Email security drivers for SMTP and POP3 authentication—negotiate authentication via a SASL (Simple Authentication and Security Layer) mechanism. These security drivers are implementations of the Uniface Security Driver API, which you can use to create your own security driver. For more information, see APIs: Security Driver . To help you use the API, the C source files for the security drivers are available as a sample on Rocket Community . The compiled libraries for the drivers provided by Uniface are located in the /common/bin (Windows) or /common/lib (Unix) directory of your Uniface installation. To make a security driver available to your application, you must specify the library and entry point in the [USER_3GL] section of the assignment file. For example: [USER_3GL] ; C/S security driver:C:/Program Files (x86)/Uniface10/bin/zsecdrv(usecappl) ; OAuth 2.0 security drivers for email:C:/Program Files (x86)/Uniface10/bin//uauthxoauth2(UAuthXOAUTH2POP, UAuthXOAUTH2SMTP) Copy Related Links APIs: Security Driver Uniface provides an API for creating custom client/server and SMTP and POP security drivers. The API include files for the C compiler and libraries are provided in the Uniface/3gl directory. SMTP and POP3 Email Uniface provides support for sending and receiving email using the SMTP and POP protocols over TCP/IP or TLS. Security Context A security context is the complete security environment required for a secure connection to a mail server. It consists of one or more security drivers that are responsible for connection and authentication to the email server. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}